[2] Global update as of 16 Nov 2011
Date: Wed 16 Nov 2011
Source: Global Polio Eradication Initiative
http://www.polioeradication.org/Dataandmonitoring/Poliothisweek.aspx


Case count as of 16 Nov 2011:
Total cases: Year-to-date 2011 / Year-to-date 2010 / Total in 2010
Globally: 520 / 789 / 1352
- endemic countries: 241 / 184 / 232
- non-endemic countries: 279 / 605 / 1120

Countries reporting new cases during past week
----------------------------------------------
- Endemic countries
Afghanistan
Six cases were reported in the past week [week ending 16 Nov 2011],
all wild poliovirus type 1 [WPV1]. The total number of cases for 2011
is now 53. 3 of the cases reported this week are in districts which
had not previously reported a case this year -- Barmal district in
Paktika province, Shahidi Hassas district in Uruzgan province, and
Daychopan in Zabul province. The case reported in Paktika is the 1st
case in the entire province for 2011. Afghanistan's most recent case
had onset of paralysis on [22 Oct 2011] (in Maywand district, Kandahar
province).

Pakistan
Nine new cases were reported in the past week (all WPV1s), from
Balochistan, Federally Administered Tribal Areas (FATA), Khyber
Pakhtunkhwa (KP), and Sindh, bringing the total number of cases for
2011 to 145. The most recent case had onset of paralysis on [19 Oct
2011] (WPV1 from KP).

[No new cases reported for the week ending 16 Nov 2011 in Nigeria and
India]

- Non-endemic countries
No new cases reported from any of the countries with 2011 transmission
-- Angola, Chad, Central African Republic, China, Democratic Republic
of the Congo, Horn of Africa (Kenya), West Africa (Cote d'Ivoire,
Guinea, Mali, and Niger).

2011 annual totals by county as of 16 Nov 2011:
Afghanistan - 53
India - 1
Pakistan - 145
Nigeria - 42
DR Congo - 86
Chad - 117
Angola - 5
Central African Republic - 2
China - 18
Guinea - 3
Kenya - 1
Cote d'Ivoire - 36
Niger - 2
Mali - 7
Congo - 1
Gabon - 1

